ver the same fissures and misunderstandings that continue to permeate American race relations more than half a century after the unforgettable photograph at Little Rock. And yet, as Margolick explains, a bond between Elizabeth and Hazel, silent but complex, endures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aInterracial friendshipxArkansasxLittle Rock. 0aInterracial friendshipzArkansaszLittle Rock. 0aSchool integrationxHistoryx20th centuryxArkansasxLittle Rock. 0aSchool integrationzArkansaszLittle RockxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030017835740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300178357423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300178357/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles